<Layout>

<section class="page">

<div class="container">


<div class="page-intro">

<span class="page-eyebrow">
Legal
</span>


<h1 class="page-title">
Refund & Cancellation Policy
</h1>


<p class="page-description">

Understand MonkeyReach's refund eligibility, cancellation process, and payment policies for digital marketing services.

</p>


</div>



<div class="page-content">



<section class="page-section">


<p>
<strong>Effective Date:</strong> June 27, 2026
</p>


<p>
<strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 27, 2026
</p>


<p>
At MonkeyReach Media, we are committed to delivering high-quality SEO and digital marketing services. This policy explains our approach to cancellations, refunds, and payment adjustments.
</p>


<p>
By making a payment or entering into a service agreement with MonkeyReach Media, you agree to this Refund & Cancellation Policy.
</p>


</section>






<section class="page-section">


<h2>
1. Nature of Our Services
</h2>


<p>
MonkeyReach provides professional digital marketing services that are:
</p>


<ul>

<li>
<strong>Time-intensive:</strong>
Research, strategy, and implementation begin after project initiation.
</li>


<li>
<strong>Long-term focused:</strong>
SEO and digital growth activities require consistent effort and time.
</li>


<li>
<strong>Customized:</strong>
Strategies are developed based on each client's industry, goals, competition, and business requirements.
</li>


</ul>


<p>
Because digital marketing services involve planning, research, and execution, certain fees become non-refundable once work has started.
</p>


</section>







<section class="page-section">


<h2>
2. Cancellation Policy
</h2>



<h3>
2.1 Monthly Retainer Plans
</h3>


<ul>

<li>
Clients may cancel monthly retainers by providing written notice.
</li>

<li>
Services continue until the end of the applicable billing period or notice period.
</li>

<li>
Payments already made for the active billing cycle are non-refundable.
</li>

</ul>





<h3>
2.2 Project-Based Services
</h3>


<ul>

<li>
Cancellation requests must be submitted in writing.
</li>


<li>
If cancellation occurs before work begins, a refund may be issued after deducting applicable payment processing fees.
</li>


<li>
If work has started, charges may apply based on completed work and resources invested.
</li>


</ul>





<h3>
2.3 One-Time Services
</h3>


<p>
One-time services may include SEO audits, keyword research, competitor analysis, and similar fixed deliverables.
</p>


<ul>

<li>
Cancellation requests before work begins may be considered.
</li>

<li>
Once work has started, refunds are generally not available.
</li>

</ul>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h2>
3. Refund Policy
</h2>


<h3>
3.1 Refund Eligibility
</h3>


<div class="page-card">


<ul>

<li>
<strong>Payment received, work not started:</strong>
Eligible for refund minus applicable processing fees.
</li>


<li>
<strong>Work in progress:</strong>
Reviewed based on project completion stage and resources invested.
</li>


<li>
<strong>Completed work or delivered services:</strong>
Not eligible for refund.
</li>


<li>
<strong>Active monthly retainer period:</strong>
Current billing period is non-refundable.
</li>


</ul>


</div>


</section>







<section class="page-section">


<h3>
3.2 Non-Refundable Items
</h3>


<p>
The following items are generally non-refundable:
</p>


<ul>

<li>
Completed services or delivered work
</li>

<li>
Third-party software, tools, or subscriptions purchased for project execution
</li>

<li>
Setup, onboarding, or consultation fees
</li>

<li>
Priority or expedited service charges
</li>

<li>
Payment processing charges
</li>

<li>
Active monthly service periods
</li>

</ul>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h3>
3.3 Exceptional Circumstances
</h3>


<p>
In exceptional situations such as verified billing errors or circumstances beyond reasonable control, refund requests may be reviewed individually.
</p>


<p>
Each request will be evaluated fairly based on the circumstances involved.
</p>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h2>
4. How To Request A Cancellation Or Refund
</h2>


<p>
To request a cancellation or refund, contact us through:
</p>


<p>

Email:

<a href="mailto:contact@monkeyreach.com">
contact@monkeyreach.com
</a>

</p>


<p>
Please include:
</p>


<ul>

<li>
Your name
</li>

<li>
Company name (if applicable)
</li>

<li>
Invoice or payment reference
</li>

<li>
Reason for your request
</li>

</ul>


<p>
We aim to acknowledge requests within 2 business days. Approved refunds will generally be processed within 7–14 business days.
</p>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h2>
5. Payment Methods & Currencies
</h2>


<p>
MonkeyReach accepts payments through approved payment methods including:
</p>


<ul>

<li>
Bank Transfer (NEFT / RTGS / IMPS)
</li>

<li>
Razorpay
</li>

<li>
Stripe
</li>

<li>
PayPal
</li>

<li>
Payoneer
</li>

</ul>


<p>
Payments may be accepted in Indian Rupees (INR) and US Dollars (USD) unless otherwise agreed.
</p>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h2>
6. Dispute Resolution
</h2>


<p>
If you are dissatisfied with a refund or cancellation decision, please contact us directly so we can attempt to resolve the matter professionally.
</p>


<p>
Disputes will be handled according to the laws of India and the jurisdiction specified in our
<a href="/terms-and-conditions">
Terms & Conditions
</a>.
</p>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h2>
7. Changes To This Policy
</h2>


<p>
MonkeyReach Media may update this Refund & Cancellation Policy periodically. Changes become effective once published on this page.
</p>


</section>








<section class="page-section">


<h2>
8. Contact Us
</h2>


<p>
For refund or cancellation-related questions:
</p>


<p>

